{"id":70058,"title":"Melanoma vaccines: mixed past, promising future.","abstract":"Cancer vaccines were one of the earliest forms of immunotherapy to be investigated. Past attempts to vaccinate against cancer, including melanoma, have mixed results, showing the complexity of what was believed to be a simple concept. However, several recent successes and the combination of improved knowledge of tumor immunology and the advent of new immunomodulators make vaccination a promising strategy for the future. ","date":"2014-09-23","categories":"Neoplasms","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25245965","annotations":[{"name":"Immunology","weight":0.812569,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunology"},{"name":"Immunotherapy","weight":0.789093,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunotherapy"},{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.783461,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"},{"name":"Vaccine","weight":0.781843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccine"},{"name":"Cancer vaccine","weight":0.727578,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_vaccine"},{"name":"Vaccination","weight":0.724688,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccination"},{"name":"Immunomodulation therapy","weight":0.460335,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunomodulation_therapy"},{"name":"Tumor","weight":0.448361,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tumor"},{"name":"Melanoma","weight":0.324541,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melanoma"},{"name":"Cancer immunology","weight":0.152227,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_immunology"},{"name":"Strategy","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strategy"},{"name":"Concept","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concept"},{"name":"Complexity","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complexity"},{"name":"Knowl